## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-195">Il <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.DataflowBlock.Encapsulate%2A> metodo richiede due blocchi esistenti: un blocco di destinazione (un'istanza di una classe che implementa <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ITargetBlock%601>) e un blocco di origine (un'istanza di una classe che implementa <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ISourceBlock%601>).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-195">The <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.DataflowBlock.Encapsulate%2A> method requires two existing blocks: a target block (an instance of a class that implements <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ITargetBlock%601>) and a source block (an instance of a class that implements <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ISourceBlock%601>).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-196"><xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.DataflowBlock.Encapsulate%2A> Crea una nuova istanza della classe interna che si connette il <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ITargetBlock%601> ai membri di interfaccia il `target` parametro e il <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ISourceBlock%601> ai membri di interfaccia di `source` parametro.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-196"><xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.DataflowBlock.Encapsulate%2A> creates a new instance of an internal class that connects the <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ITargetBlock%601> interface members to the `target` parameter and the <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ISourceBlock%601> interface members to the `source` parameter.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-197">Entrambe <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ITargetBlock%601> e <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ISourceBlock%601> derivano da <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.IDataflowBlock>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-197">Both <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ITargetBlock%601> and <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ISourceBlock%601> derive from <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.IDataflowBlock>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-198">Completamento dei blocchi è passato in modo esplicito dalle origini alle destinazioni.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-198">Block completion is explicitly passed from sources to targets.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-199">Pertanto, il <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.IDataflowBlock.Complete%2A> e <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.IDataflowBlock.Fault%2A> metodi sono connesso alla destinazione durante il <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.IDataflowBlock.Completion%2A> proprietà è connesso all'origine.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-199">Therefore, the <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.IDataflowBlock.Complete%2A> and <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.IDataflowBlock.Fault%2A> methods are connected to the target while the <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.IDataflowBlock.Completion%2A> property is connected to the source.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-200">È necessario assicurarsi che quando la destinazione metà viene completato, l'origine della metà Ottiene completata in modo più appropriato. Per esempio:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-200">You must ensure that when the target half  completes, the source half gets completed in the most appropriate manner; for example:</span></span>  
  
 `target.Completion.ContinueWith(completion => source.Complete());`  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-201">In alternativa, se si desidera propagare il tipo di completamento, è possibile usare questo codice più sofisticato:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-201">Or, if you want to propagate the completion type, you can use this more sophisticated code:</span></span>  
  
```  
target.Completion.ContinueWith(completion => { if (completion.IsFaulted)    
  
((IDataflowBlock)batchBlock).Fault(completion.Exception);   
else   
batchBlock.Complete();   
});  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-202">È necessario fornire anche in modo esplicito la propagazione del messaggio dalla destinazione all'origine.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-202">You must also explicitly provide the message propagation from target to source.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-203">Il vantaggio di questa connessione esplicita è che offre la libertà di eseguire l'elaborazione senza vincolato tra i due blocchi incapsulati.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-203">The benefit of this explicit connection is that it gives you the freedom to perform any unconstrained processing between the two encapsulated blocks.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-204">È possibile eseguire che codifica l'elaborazione necessaria in delegati dei blocchi (se i blocchi accettano delegati) oppure incorporando una rete secondaria dei blocchi tra di essi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-204">You may do that either by encoding the necessary processing into the blocks' delegates (if the blocks take delegates), or by embedding a sub-network of blocks between them.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="de2ae-205">Il modo più semplice consiste nell'usare un blocco che accetta i delegati; ad esempio, usare <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ActionBlock%601>, <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.TransformBlock%602>, <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.TransformManyBlock%602> (se applicabile), o un blocco personalizzato.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="de2ae-205">The easier way is to use a block that takes delegates; for example, use <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.ActionBlock%601>, <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.TransformBlock%602>, <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Dataflow.TransformManyBlock%602> (if applicable), or a custom block.</span></span>

